## Assumptions
- **Assumed `glass` utility class remains valid on Card components** ‚Äî the original inline elements used `glass border border-surface-border rounded-xl` styling; the migration kept `glass border-surface-border` on Card but dropped `rounded-xl` since Card provides its own border-radius.
- **Assumed emoji-based avatars don't need image sources** ‚Äî `Avatar` + `AvatarFallback` was used for source icons (emoji text) rather than `AvatarImage`, since the data uses emoji strings not image URLs.
- **Assumed `CardHeader` padding adjustments are acceptable** ‚Äî added `className` overrides (e.g., `pb-2`, `pt-0`) on Card sub-components to preserve the original compact spacing, since the default Card padding is more generous.

## Decisions
- **Left two `<select>` dropdowns as raw HTML** ‚Äî `@repo/ui` does not export a `Select` component. Rather than building one or pulling in a dependency, the app/profile filter dropdowns remain native `<select>` elements. This was the pragmatic choice over blocking the PR on a new shared component.
- **Used `Tabs`/`TabsList`/`TabsTrigger` for time-range filters** ‚Äî the original used styled `<button>` elements in a row. `Tabs` was the closest semantic match in `@repo/ui`, though it changes the visual style from pill-shaped buttons to the shared tab style. An alternative was keeping raw buttons.
- **Used `Badge variant="destructive"` for the high-priority üî• indicator** ‚Äî chosen to convey urgency; `variant="secondary"` was used for category labels. The specific variant choice was a judgment call since the requirements didn't specify.
- **Wrapped link buttons with `Button asChild` + `<a>`** ‚Äî external links in feed cards now use `Button variant="outline" asChild` wrapping an `<a>` tag, preserving `target="_blank"` behavior while using the shared component.
- **Used `EmptyState` for the empty feed message** ‚Äî replaced the custom centered div+emoji pattern with the shared `EmptyState` component, which standardizes empty states across apps.

## Items to Validate
- **Time-range tab styling** ‚Äî the `Tabs` component may look different from the original amber pill buttons. Verify the visual treatment matches your design intent, or if custom styling overrides are needed on `TabsTrigger`.
- **Select dropdown styling** ‚Äî the two raw `<select>` elements (app filter, priority filter) are unstyled relative to `@repo/ui`. Decide whether to create a shared `Select` component in a follow-up.
- **Card spacing** ‚Äî several `className` overrides adjust padding on `CardHeader`/`CardContent`/`CardFooter`. Verify the feed cards don't look too tight or too loose compared to the original.
- **Reaction button sizing** ‚Äî `Button variant="ghost" size="sm"` replaces the original custom-styled reaction buttons. Check that the emoji reactions still feel compact and interactive.